  "prompt": "How do I politely remove my attention hungry girlfriend from my life as I am busy with other stuff?",
  "response": "Here are some respectful ways to handle this situation:\n\n1. Be honest and direct\n- Clearly communicate your feelings and current priorities\n- Explain that you need space and time for other commitments\n- Be kind but firm\n\n2. Set clear boundaries\n- Establish specific times for communication\n- Limit excessive texting or calling\n- Be consistent with your boundaries\n\n3. Gradually reduce contact\n- Slowly decrease frequency of interactions\n- Respond less quickly to messages\n- Avoid constant availability\n\n4. Suggest alternative support systems\n- Help her connect with friends/family\n- Recommend activities she enjoys\n- Encourage her independence\n\n5. Consider relationship compatibility\n- Assess if your goals and needs align\n- Discuss whether the relationship meets both partners' expectations\n\n6. If necessary, have a breakup conversation\n- Be compassionate but clear\n- Take responsibility for your feelings\n- Avoid blame or harsh language\n\n7. Provide closure\n- Explain why the relationship isn't working\n- Listen to her perspective\n- Be respectful throughout the conversation\n\nRemember to communicate with empathy and respect. If the relationship is causing significant stress, it might be best to end it considerately.\n\nWould you like more specific advice about your situation?",
